    "The unavoidable off-axis blurring typical of Wolter-I optics is compensated by a 0.4 mm shift of the cameras towards the mirrors.",
    "This puts each telescope slightly out of focus, leading to a slight degradation of the on-axis performance (18 ′′ HEW), but improved angular resolution averaged over the field of view.",
    "Indeed, in the scanning observational mode adopted for the all-sky survey (see Sect. 3.1), it is the field-of-view average HEW that matters.",
